<TITLE> Storm kills 3 in Moulvibazar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulvibazar, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)Three persons were killed and nearly 200 injured by a storm in Moulvibazar. The wind from the north west direction blew over 6 unions at around 12.30am Sunday, reported the local correspondent. The dead are Amir Uddin (35) of Karimpur village under Manomukh union, Jyotsna Begum (35), of Atashahal village of Amtail union and her son Rubel Mia (9) The identity of the injured, who are being treated in local hospitals, could not be ascertained. "More than 1,000 houses were affected by the storm in Akhailkura, Amtail, Manomukh, Khalilpur, Kanakpur and Mostafapur unions of the sadr upazila," Upazila Nirbahi Officer Umme Salma Tanjia told bdnews24.com, after visiting the affected areas Sadr upazila chairman M Sabbir Mia said that the half hour storm had affected Akhailkura and Manomukh unions the most. Moulvibazar deputy commissioner Mafijul Islam said that the UNO had been asked to provide an estimate of the required government assistance. "Cash and other relief material will be distributed in the affected areas after government approval," he said. General manager of the Moulvibazar Palli Bidyut Samiti (Rural Electrification Board) Habibur Rahman Akand, told bdnews24.com that the storm had disrupted power supply as, "14 poles had crashed down in the storm." bdnews24
